{{italic title}}
<!-- Discuss before changing this to an infobox. This is a painting with a lot of intricate detail and looks like an incomprehensible smear at infobox default size -->[[File:Jacob_Isaacksz._van_Ruisdael_-_The_Breakwater_-_WGA20503.jpg|right|upright=1.8|thumb|''Storm Off a Sea Coast'' also known as ''The Breakwater'' by [[Jacob van Ruisdael]]|alt=Painting of a coastal scene with ships in stormy weather]]

'''''Storm Off a Sea Coast''''', also known as '''''The Breakwater''''', is a 1670 [[oil painting|oil]] on canvas painting by the [[Dutch Golden Age painting|Dutch Golden Age painter]] [[Jacob van Ruisdael]]. It is in the collection of the [[Louvre]] in Paris.{{sfn|Slive|2001|p=460}}

The painting is called ''A Storm at Sea Off the Dykes of Holland'' in the 1911 catalogue raisonné by [[Hofstede de Groot]]; it is catalogue number 961. He wrote "On the right is a dyke lined with piles, beyond which is a fisherman's cottage with a few trees. On the left corner of the dyke, great waves are breaking. Farther back rise the masts of several large vessels, as well as the stern with a Dutch flag." {{sfn|Hofstede de Groot|1911|p=296}} The painting is called ''Storm Off a Sea Coast'' in Slive's 2001 catalogue raisonné of Ruisdael, catalogue number 653.{{sfn|Slive|2001|p=461}} 

In the 19th century [[Vincent van Gogh]] called this painting by Ruisdael, along with ''The Bush'' and ''Ray of Light'', "magnificent".{{sfn|Jansen|Luijten|Bakker|2009|loc=[http://vangoghletters.org/vg/letters/let034/letter.html Letter 34]}} 

The Louvre has in French: "L'Estacade ou Gros temps sur une digue de Hollande, dit aussi Une tempête". Its inventory number is INV. 1818. Its dimensions are 110 cm x 160 cm.<ref name="Louvre">{{cite web|title=The Louvre|url=http://cartelfr.louvre.fr/cartelfr/visite?srv=car_not_frame&idNotice=25885|publisher=[[Louvre]]|accessdate=13 December 2015}}</ref>

